40|$|The {{impact of}} life on the {{atmosphere}} is examined through a discussion of the budgets of important <b>atmospheric</b> <b>constituents</b> and the processes that control their concentrations. Life profoundly influences oxygen and a number of minor <b>atmospheric</b> <b>constituents,</b> but many important gases, including those with the greatest effect on global climate, appear to be little altered by biological processes, at least in the steady state...|$|R
